<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_1beb6f94-d0d6-4084-8fc2-249702c1edb3" outputclass="ncc-clause"><sptc>B5D2</sptc><title id="_466847b0-e662-459e-999a-5053893ad4a0">Drinking water service</title><subclause id="_26f2d303-fcc7-4c5a-a263-c0c5c92bf8ae" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_9ae25a6e-9e49-4be3-aece-93648092c929">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A hazard exists wherever it is possible for water or <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1228_0.6.0.xml#_a7483c3c-cd8a-4c37-8f2b-8e4fba0e0989" id="_c4de5b15-37cb-4dfe-9ace-b081f9479fab" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">contaminants</xref> to enter a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1250_0.7.0.xml#_762d6a54-e28c-400b-b9c5-5fceac019a05" id="_c6efffcf-03f7-412d-beba-5da8d25299ab" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">drinking water</xref> service or supply via any potential or actual <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1233_1.0.0.xml#_b3f409ec-8f72-48d9-8a64-0dc9d5fb5d67" id="_1fe84fa5-da08-47ff-afdc-efc50700cbf4" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">cross-connection</xref> between—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_cd23acb5-7044-4a38-a4ec-3013e53a6bfb">The <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1250_0.7.0.xml#_762d6a54-e28c-400b-b9c5-5fceac019a05" id="_625dae09-bfbf-41ab-ba80-e4d3026bf8be" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">drinking water</xref> service; and</li><li id="_fe597ba4-2b2b-4d43-9565-e23fe1231c0e">Any of the following:<ol><li>A <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1378_4.3.0.xml#_cfc4fec0-3cb7-41d6-b176-4a92d4cdb221" id="_e1dd8200-3844-471b-bba4-4badf0e642de" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">non-drinking water</xref> service.</li><li>A <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1422_4.4.0.xml#_bd764954-3054-4109-81f2-164feefc5058" id="_371892f9-5723-43e9-92e1-09747a64f4b7" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">rainwater service</xref>.</li><li>An alternative water supply,.</li><li>A <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1487_0.7.0.xml#_4cbd9e00-0622-4dfd-9de4-913c80257732" id="_4f83548e-35a6-4523-bf32-6cb07fd6726c" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">swimming pool</xref>.</li><li>Pipes, fixtures or specialist equipment (including <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1210_0.10.0.xml#_5e4c02dd-0737-47ed-ad7b-5de888c05ed7" id="_59ad60d4-50b1-45f1-aff2-d317e4fdd82a" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">boilers</xref> and pumps) containing chemicals, liquids, gases or other substances which may be harmful to health or safety.</li></ol></li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_c9e2fa9d-300f-4321-8957-d245750eca8a" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_190e617d-b578-4c5d-bd88-d50be582a8e5">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>Each hazard must—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_6b4b96da-f38b-4bbe-b89b-4daf7e6fb6f6">Be assigned—<ol><li>an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1349_3.0.0.xml#_9f04cdcd-91b5-41a3-81b7-1243261eb779" id="_c4ee9b4a-2b32-4c9b-9c2b-bb78c7e1aced" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Individual protection</xref> <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1332_3.6.0.xml#_e221b82c-bc4b-43d2-ab64-522dd5dd1885" id="_3a547deb-25f7-413c-9f32-40e3f18ba349" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">Hazard Rating</xref> in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/9560_0.38.0.xml#_d1893ae5-5ac7-4a10-aacb-a5fc6257e0fa" id="_42d0f62c-5993-4ac3-a4b9-3853d2c4898b" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="subclause">B5D7(4)</xref>, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/9560_0.38.0.xml#_c1dbfb38-5d34-4076-9f48-c913d5092d82" id="_f6e88c81-2a95-4f98-900c-40af3539c5d0" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">(5)</xref>,or <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/9560_0.38.0.xml#_c1dbfb38-5d34-4076-9f48-c913d5092d82" id="_ebb1cdbf-ec94-4132-9017-a9afbe6e522c" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">(6)</xref>; or</li><li>a Zone protection Hazard Rating in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/9560_0.38.0.xml#_c2096160-5c8e-40bc-bb1d-b6814ab7ee26" id="_b303bfb1-3853-4931-9ed3-966aeac0c0a6" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="subclause">B5D7(7)</xref>, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/9560_0.38.0.xml#_01655ab8-55a0-48de-8910-fc5d7214893c" id="_b10d082a-890e-4fd4-983b-072bb877d963" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="subclause">(8)</xref>, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/9560_0.38.0.xml#_05da5774-48b9-4eae-a61f-187fd924b4ff" id="_707fa70c-15d5-4934-a41a-9659f94d5f9e" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="subclause">(9)</xref>; and</li></ol></li><li id="_cd8fadf9-e1a2-4ceb-b819-7d06f6c5a433">Be isolated from the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1250_0.7.0.xml#_762d6a54-e28c-400b-b9c5-5fceac019a05" id="_ed097651-1881-427e-9c70-ab74f7421d8d" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">drinking water</xref> service by an appropriate <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1204_1.0.0.xml#_0fd1c6f9-50b2-4e0c-bda6-25c2bf33379f" id="_5f0b4d0b-6d59-459d-8135-e1b9e9b872e3" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">backflow prevention device</xref> which is selected and installed in accordance with Section 4 of AS/NZS 3500.1.</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_1f393a7a-0c81-4745-bbb8-c2c043bbfa7c" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_7b199380-e151-4762-9afe-6d10cdeccaaa">SubClause</title><num>3</num><p>Where a site is served by a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1376_4.2.0.xml#_12d6153c-4986-4856-80c0-e21bb57af12f" id="_0f93a2ea-6b1d-4085-ba95-8fb185c60a26" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">Network Utility Operator’s</xref> <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1250_0.7.0.xml#_762d6a54-e28c-400b-b9c5-5fceac019a05" id="_89bb9786-5173-4704-a990-13aefd6aebff" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">drinking water</xref>, appropriate <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1227_1.0.0.xml#_f80df168-6569-4558-86ed-6d4b94202ea0" id="_a18a9ed4-c289-4d5a-922c-d80e1c7e9129" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">containment protection</xref> must be: </p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_bb46bf6e-545a-4768-84be-efb709b6805f">selected and installed in accordance with the Network Utility Operators relevant regulations, guidelines, policies or similar documents; or</li><li id="_be930f92-f7fb-41bc-b181-026b3aa87b82">where the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1376_4.2.0.xml#_12d6153c-4986-4856-80c0-e21bb57af12f" id="_ddfb9295-e430-4534-9626-a2e6d006fffb" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Network Utility Operator</xref> does not prescribe requirements for <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1227_1.0.0.xml#_f80df168-6569-4558-86ed-6d4b94202ea0" id="_2ec70b06-7c2c-4815-9610-803774982f4c" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">containment protection</xref>, assign a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1227_1.0.0.xml#_f80df168-6569-4558-86ed-6d4b94202ea0" id="_16549c86-333d-4277-b67f-daeb5fa263ed" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Containment protection</xref> <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1332_3.6.0.xml#_e221b82c-bc4b-43d2-ab64-522dd5dd1885" id="_e51e8e07-dc03-4577-938d-3ce2f075c44d" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Hazard Rating</xref> in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/9560_0.38.0.xml#_c1dbfb38-5d34-4076-9f48-c913d5092d82" id="_14529740-3f64-4f0f-8af6-d868468416a6" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">B5D7 (10)</xref>, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/9560_0.38.0.xml#_c1dbfb38-5d34-4076-9f48-c913d5092d82" id="_b9cc09d2-c5fb-414d-95ef-b72e60370e75" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">(11)</xref> or <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/9560_0.38.0.xml#_c1dbfb38-5d34-4076-9f48-c913d5092d82" id="_cc37b367-04ab-460a-83de-726a030ac12f" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">(12)</xref>, and select and install appropriate <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1227_1.0.0.xml#_f80df168-6569-4558-86ed-6d4b94202ea0" id="_03102e16-c811-4a46-8499-14953ef7f019" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">containment protection</xref> in accordance with Section 4 of AS/NZS 3500.1</li></ol></subclause><callout id="_47c6a858-3022-42ae-b07b-1399ea625ec7"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>Where a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1227_1.0.0.xml#_f80df168-6569-4558-86ed-6d4b94202ea0" id="_03d1019a-035c-43df-8120-b577667a1534" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Containment protection</xref> <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1204_1.0.0.xml#_0fd1c6f9-50b2-4e0c-bda6-25c2bf33379f" id="_061b5728-3240-4b46-8d17-8ed55e460e7b" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">backflow prevention device</xref> is installed external of a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1376_4.2.0.xml#_12d6153c-4986-4856-80c0-e21bb57af12f" id="_b0ffa28d-560e-47f7-98ef-92ee768e8678" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Network Utility Operator</xref> water meter, the valve remains the responsibility of the property owner unless owned by the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1376_4.2.0.xml#_12d6153c-4986-4856-80c0-e21bb57af12f" id="_66f652d4-9b9f-480b-9488-0c4835696df1" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Network Utility Operator</xref>, including any testing, servicing and maintenance that may be required.</p><p>Where the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1376_4.2.0.xml#_12d6153c-4986-4856-80c0-e21bb57af12f" id="_7cf97107-f87f-4451-9069-6800c6dea082" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Network Utility Operator</xref> prescribes <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1227_1.0.0.xml#_f80df168-6569-4558-86ed-6d4b94202ea0" id="_8b43bf20-2e3b-403e-877c-7bcbdbf35725" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">containment protection</xref> <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1332_3.6.0.xml#_e221b82c-bc4b-43d2-ab64-522dd5dd1885" id="_a03e41b8-9688-4b54-ad9c-1f4a0b6856a7" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">hazard ratings</xref> above the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1332_3.6.0.xml#_e221b82c-bc4b-43d2-ab64-522dd5dd1885" id="_97a7fb39-08ad-460c-90ea-345bdee2db12" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">hazard rating</xref> set out in B5D7 (10), (11), and (12), the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1376_4.2.0.xml#_12d6153c-4986-4856-80c0-e21bb57af12f" id="_bb598297-afba-4c29-a4e6-ff174a7ad23f" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Network Utility Operator</xref> is responsible for the regulation of the containment backflow installation.</p></callout><callout id="_b16155b3-12e4-4322-92e8-e1309d39d54d"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>No additional individual or zone protection backflow prevention protection is required where cross-connection mitigation is provided in accordance with AS/NZS 3500.1 as an integral part of a fixture, appliance or apparatus and is suitable for the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1332_3.6.0.xml#_e221b82c-bc4b-43d2-ab64-522dd5dd1885" id="_b26bc63c-884b-4b33-86a2-8a9af4565110" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Hazard Rating</xref> specified in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/9560_0.38.0.xml#_c1dbfb38-5d34-4076-9f48-c913d5092d82" id="_b9a31060-efcb-4f23-8dd5-1a4b4939c1e5" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">B5D7</xref>.</p></callout></clause>